Commands to install database
sudo apt update
sudo apt install postgresql
sudo apt install postgresql-contrib

Commands to run database
sudo service postgresql start
sudo -u postgres psql

Config of the database itself

CREATE DATABASE SongsDatabase;

\c songsdatabase; (when the database is created, it's lower case sensitive for \c)

CREATE TABLE media (
user_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
owner VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
format VARCHAR(10) NOT NULL,
artist VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
title VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
genre1 VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
);

This 3 lines are missing on media table, will have a later implementation adding them, but this is how they'll look like
genre2 VARCHAR(100),                   
lyrics VARCHAR(1000) NOT NULL,            
audiobase64 VARCHAR(1000) NOT NULL


INSERT INTO media (owner, format, artist, title, genre1) VALUES
